description:
&lt;p&gt;We are a busy acute admissions unit with 26 Inpatient beds, which is also home to the 4 bed Paediatric High Dependency care unit. The inpatient wards offer medical, surgical, orthopaedic, ENT, and Max Fax services. The inpatient wards sit alongside our busy assessment unit further supported by the children&#39;s community nursing team. We also support a busy children’s phlebotomy clinic. Alongside this we have a very busy outpatients department &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for motivated Healthcare Assistants to join our team to assist the Registered Nurses in the delivery of care to babies/children/young people and their families. You must be able to communicate effectively with babies, children, families and members of the multi disciplinary Team. You will have experience of caring in a hospital environment or have worked with children in another setting. We are a friendly Unit and are committed to providing a high standard of care to our patients. Shifts are 12 hours and rotation between days/nights/weekends.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Irene: &quot;After working on the bank in 2 different hospitals in a variety of setting I thought I had worked in every possible environment but the Children&#39;s Unit has been different to all the others. The staff are nice and fun to work with with approachable managers.&quot; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you fit the above specification we would like to hear from you.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If this job requires you to have a DBS check to enable you to properly fulfil the requirements of the job, on appointment you will be required to repay the cost of obtaining a DBS check and this amount will be reclaimed from your salary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 08/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alison Green (Sister)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: alison.green@uhd.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0300 019 2029&lt;/p&gt;
